This is related to BIC. So, can this handler move to biccommands.cpp ?

This handler would be used in BMC to get BIC GPIO state.

However, handlers in biccommands.cpp are used to handle the IPMI command sending from BIC.

Thus, we think this handler should be put in oemcommands.cpp not biccommands.cpp.

oemcommands.cpp file has oem netn 0x30, .., 0x36. Netfn 0x38 is bridge IC commands specific netfn.

I think biccommands.cpp is specifically created to have bic specific commands handlers and also for easy maintenance and understanding.

I suggest to move this code to biccommands.cpp file.

Hi Michael,

Which one do you prefer?
I agree with Kumar.  If the current design is to place all the BIC commands in biccommands.cpp, we should keep them there and place more general, non-BIC commands in the oemcommands.cpp file.

```
-const std::vector<uint8_t> iana = {0x15, 0xA0, 0x0}; // Meta IANA
+static constexpr auto iana = std::array<uint8_t, 3>{0x15, 0xA0, 0x0}; // Meta IANA
```

This doesn't seem like a very reasonable command as it is providing no abstraction and is effectively just a raw passthru.  Don't we know the format of any of the req/resp data that we can reply with real parsed values?
Need to add doc around this OEM command to define what it does similar to what is shown on lines 73-77.

Let's add something like this so we can clean up the code everywhere:

`using Iana = std::array<uint8_t, 3>;`
We add this definition to commandutils.hpp file
Please add to a proper header file.  I see this is currently declared in `usb-dbg.cpp`.  Does it need to be moved to something BIC-centric?
Referring to appcommands.cpp and oemcommands.cpp, they just declare "sendBicCmd" function on the top of file instead of including usb-dbg.hpp.
Please clean them all up in a follow up commit then.  It is poor practice to forward declare some other C-part's functions.
Should this be `std::array<uint8_t, 3>` (or Iana type I proposed earlier)?

The reqIana will be the parameter to sendBicCmd function.

But the sendBicCmd needs vector as input type.

So if we use std::array<uint8_t, 3> as the input in this handler, we must convert reqIana into vector first, then pass into sendBicCmd.
Let's make this common with the one you defined earlier.  Maybe move to a common header that isn't related to the BIC.

Hi all,

Do you have any concern?
Please clean this up as well.  There's no reason for C-style #defines when we added a type for this.
